[0.000, "o", "                                                                                                                                        \u001b[0m\u001b]8;;\u0007\r\r\n\u001b[2K \u001b[1m\u001b[3m\u001b[38;2;108;108;108mAnalyzing RNG output\u001b[39m\u001b[23m\u001b[22m                                                                                                                                                      \u001b[0m\u001b]8;;\u0007\r\r\n\u001b[2K                                                                                                                                                                           \u001b[0m\u001b]8;;\u0007\r\r\n\u001b[2K \u001b[3m\u001b[38;2;108;108;108mI'm currently looking at tests that expect a late-life failure at RNG 99. It seems the hard stepwise chance at 48 months gives a 16% probability, which might not be      \u001b[0m\u001b]8;;\u0007\r\r\n\u001b[2K \u001b[3;38;2;108;108;108menough for RNG 99. I need to inspect the RNG output for state 99, and it might be beneficial to consider an older tick at 59 months, which still falls under index 4. If  \u001b[0m\u001b]8;;\u0007\r\r\n\u001b[2K \u001b[3;38;2;108;108;108mI look at 6"]
