[0.000, "o", "                                                                                                                     \u001b[0m\u001b]8;;\u0007\r\r\n                                                                                                                                                                           \u001b[0m\u001b]8;;\u0007\r\r\n \u001b[3m\u001b[38;2;108;108;108mI need to update the game logic in phase 1. I’ll inspect the GameState usages to identify any missing difficulty that could break tests. The design config should ideally \u001b[0m\u001b]8;;\u0007\r\r\n \u001b[3;38;2;108;108;108mbe in balance/difficulty.ts, even though the plan mentions constants/difficulty.ts, which doesn’t exist. I’ll consider exporting from balance/index and updating the      \u001b[0m\u001b]8;;\u0007\r\r\n \u001b[3;38;2;108;108;108mREADME since the public API has changed as per AGENTS. Lastly, for old saves lacking GameState, I’ll need to think of a migration or compatibility solution.\u001b[39m\u001b[23m              \u001b[0m\u001b]8;;\u0007\r\r\n                                                                           "]
[0.000, "o", "                                                                                                \u001b[0m\u001b]8;;\u0007\r\r\n \u001b[1m\u001b[3m\u001b[38;2;108;108;108mHandling save versions\u001b[39m\u001b[23m\u001b[22m                                                                                                                                                    \u001b[0m\u001b]8;;\u0007\r\r\n                                                                                                                                                                           \u001b[0m\u001b]8;;\u0007\r\r\n \u001b[3m\u001b[38;2;108;108;108mI’m considering a summary suggesting to add a safe optional field, but the plan specifies a top-level flag in the serialized state. I have to manage old saves—currently, \u001b[0m\u001b]8;;\u0007\r\r\n \u001b[3;38;2;108;108;108mwe're on save version 6. If we keep this version and an old save is missing difficulty, it could break code. \u001b[39m\u001b[23m                                                             \u001b[0m\u001b]8;;\u0007\r\r\n                                                                               "]
[0.000, "o", "                                                                                            \u001b[0m\u001b]8;;\u0007\r\r\n \u001b[3m\u001b[38;2;108;108;108mI might bump the SAVE_VERSION to 7 and default difficult settings for migration. AGENTS recommend updating migration behavior, and I need to inspect any tests expecting  \u001b[0m\u001b]8;;\u0007\r\r\n \u001b[3;38;2;108;108;108moutdated version numbers to ensure everything aligns. So, implementing a migration with updates for version 7 seems like the best path forward!\u001b[39m\u001b[23m                           \u001b[0m\u001b]8;;\u0007\r\r\n                                                                                                                                                                           \u001b[0m\u001b]8;;\u0007\r\r\n \u001b[1m\u001b[3m\u001b[38;2;108;108;108mPlanning the difficulty selector\u001b[39m\u001b[23m\u001b[22m                                                                                                                                          \u001b[0m\u001b]8;;\u0007\r\r\n                                                                                       "]
[0.000, "o", "                                                                                    \u001b[0m\u001b]8;;\u0007\r\r\n \u001b[3m\u001b[38;2;108;108;108mI need to create a difficulty selector and probably implement it in phases, committing each step individually. Phase 1 has 2 steps, Phase 2 has 5 steps, and Phase 3 has  \u001b[0m\u001b]8;;\u0007\r\r\n \u001b[3;38;2;108;108;108m3 steps, totaling 10 commits. I’m thinking about whether to commit and push after each step. While the guidance suggests doing both, the user only mentioned committing   \u001b[0m\u001b]8;;\u0007\r\r\n \u001b[3;38;2;108;108;108mevery step. Pushing after each might be heavy on the workflow, but if it helps with clarity, that could work too. I just need to keep moving forward!\u001b[39m\u001b[23m                     \u001b[0m\u001b]8;;\u0007\r\r\n                                                                                                                                                                           \u001b[0m\u001b]8;;\u0007\r\r\n \u001b[1m\u001b[3m\u001b[38;2;108;108;108mPlanning game updates\u001b[39m\u001b[23m\u001b[22m                                                  "]
