[0.000, "o", "                                                                                                                                                             \u001b[49m\u001b[0m\u001b]8;;\u0007\r\r\n\u001b[0m\u001b]8;;\u0007\r\r\n \u001b[1m\u001b[3m\u001b[38;2;108;108;108mImplementing difficulty settings\u001b[39m\u001b[23m\u001b[22m                                                                                                                                          \u001b[0m\u001b]8;;\u0007\r\r\n                                                                                                                                                                           \u001b[0m\u001b]8;;\u0007\r\r\n \u001b[3m\u001b[38;2;108;108;108mI need to minimize tool calls, but we’re still in phase one, so I won’t prune anything yet. Let’s move to step 3.1 where the CLI command will accept a difficulty flag of \u001b[0m\u001b]8;;\u0007\r\r\n \u001b[3;38;2;108;108;108measy or hard. A helper function for validation should be necessary, along with updating result text in JSON. \u001b[39m\u001b[23m                                                             \u001b[0m\u001b]8;;\u0007\r"]
[0.000, "o", "\r\n                                                                                                                                                                           \u001b[0m\u001b]8;;\u0007\r\r\n \u001b[3m\u001b[38;2;108;108;108mIn step 3.2, I’ll focus on including difficulty in the status view and possibly adjusting the TUI layout. I’ll need updates in protocol and formatting throughout. Then   \u001b[0m\u001b]8;;\u0007\r\r\n \u001b[3;38;2;108;108;108mfor 3.3, I'll set up the createFreshSession function, considering how to handle selected difficulties in the UI. It's more work, but I think it's manageable.\u001b[39m\u001b[23m             \u001b[0m\u001b]8;;\u0007\r\r\n                                                                                                                                                                           \u001b[0m\u001b]8;;\u0007\r\r\n \u001b[1m\u001b[3m\u001b[38;2;108;108;108mSimplifying the start screen\u001b[39m\u001b[23m\u001b[22m                                                                                                                                              \u001b[0m\u001b]8;;\u0007\r\r\n  "]
[0.000, "o", "                                                                                                                                                                         \u001b[0m\u001b]8;;\u0007\r\r\n \u001b[3m\u001b[38;2;108;108;108mTo simplify, I’m thinking about making the start screen feature buttons labeled \"Play Easy\" and \"Play Hard.\" This might be user-friendly, but I could also keep it        \u001b[0m\u001b]8;;\u0007\r\r\n \u001b[3;38;2;108;108;108msimpler with just \"Play\" or \"New Game\" for testing. Ideally, I'd include a radio button or toggle while retaining the button labels.\u001b[39m\u001b[23m                                      \u001b[0m\u001b]8;;\u0007\r\r\n                                                                                                                                                                           \u001b[0m\u001b]8;;\u0007\r\r\n \u001b[3m\u001b[38;2;108;108;108mI need to create an app session based on the user’s choice and difficulty level, and make updates to the top bar for displaying the difficulty badge. Careful file edits  \u001b[0m\u001b]8;;\u0007\r\r\n \u001b[3;38;2;108;108;108mare"]
[0.000, "o", " needed here; I want to manage this in steps and commit each change while running tests along the way.\u001b[39m\u001b[23m                                                                 \u001b[0m\u001b]8;;\u0007\r\r\n\u001b[0m\u001b]8;;\u0007\r\r\n\u001b[48;2;232;240;232m                                                                                                                                                                           \u001b[49m\u001b[0m\u001b]8;;\u0007\r\r\n\u001b[48;2;232;240;232m \u001b[39m\u001b[1medit\u001b[22m\u001b[39m \u001b[38;2;90;128;128mpackages/cli/src/commands/new-load.ts\u001b[39m                                                                                                                                \u001b[49m\u001b[0m\u001b]8;;\u0007\r\r\n\u001b[48;2;232;240;232m                                                                                                                                                                           \u001b[49m\u001b[0m\u001b]8;;\u0007\r\r\n\u001b[48;2;232;240;232m \u001b[38;2;108;108;108m   1 import fs from \"node:fs\";\u001b[39m                                                                                 "]
